traceability.evidence:
In src/filter-by-security.js, the function completely ignores the configured prodMinSeverity/devMinSeverity when deciding to filter a row. It simply does:

  if (vulnCount !== 0) {
    include = false;
    filterReasonMap.set(name, 'security');
  }

and never inspects actual vulnerability severities from `checkVulnerabilities`. There are no code paths or tests that gate filtering based on the configured threshold (e.g. allow low/moderate when threshold is 'high').
